text: Eve Thomas (born 9 February 2001) is a New Zealand swimmer. She competed for New Zealand in the women's 800 metre freestyle at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. Thomas is the daughter of British swimmer Sarah Hardcastle. ==References== Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:New Zealand female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:New Zealand female freestyle swimmers
